==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Poncelet
<hw>Ponce"let</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[After Jean Victor
<etsep>Poncelet</etsep>, French engineer.]</ety> <fld>(Physics)</fld>
<def>A unit of power, being the power obtained from an expenditure of
one hundred kilogram-meters of energy per second. One poncelet equals
<it>g</it> watts, when <it>g</it> is the value of the acceleration of
gravity in centimeters.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Poncho</ent>⟦br⟧
